    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "List comprehensions, like `[x*2 for x in data]`, build the *entire* resulting list in memory at once, which is what causes the MemoryError with huge files. Generators, on the other hand, are lazy; they yield one item at a time as requested, like a stream. This means they only hold one element in memory at any given moment, making them much more memory-efficient for massive datasets. For your CSV processing, switching to a generator-based approach will likely solve your memory crunch.",
      "source": "target",
