      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "While generators themselves are generally very safe and don't typically cause traditional memory leaks, you still need to be mindful of the surrounding code, especially when dealing with file handles or external resources. If you forget to close a file handle, that resource might remain open, consuming system memory, even if the generator itself is done. To spot unnecessary memory usage, use profiling tools like `memory_profiler` in Python; these tools let you monitor memory consumption line-by-line while your script is running.",
